      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Comparison Across Five Operating Points",
      "description": "Predicted RH values from the CFD model were compared against experimental measurements at five flow-speed combinations. All five operating points yielded RH < 1 relative to the predicate device, satisfying the acceptance criterion. The mesh independence study (conducted as a precursor verification step) confirmed that discretization error contributed less than 2.1% GCI to the QoI, lending confidence to the validation outcomes. Maximum RH discrepancy between simulation and experiment was 8.3% at the highest rotational speed condition, within the agreed 15% tolerance band.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/experimental-validation-run-cpb-2025",
