      "name": "Pump Pressure Head Validation at Nominal Operating Conditions",
      "description": "Simulated pump pressure head was validated against bench-top hydraulic measurements at three flow rates (3, 5, and 7 L/min) at 3000 RPM. Agreement was within 6% across all conditions. This result supports the fidelity of the CFD model for hemodynamic quantities of interest relevant to the CPB COU. Evidence for this validation result was generated by the experimental hydraulic characterization activity.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/hydraulic-bench-characterization-2025",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Max pressure head deviation: 5.8% at 7 L/min",
      "acceptanceMet": true
    }
